    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n187" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀείδω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀϝείδω</span>), fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀείσομαι</span>,
          aor. ind. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄεισε</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄεισον</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀεῖσαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">sing</span>—I. trans., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παιήονα, κλέα ἀνδρῶν</span>, ‘lays of heroes;’ also
          w. acc. of the theme of minstrelsy, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μῆνιν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 1.1</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Ἀχαιῶν
            νόστον</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.326</span></i>; with
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὡς</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            8.514</span></i>; acc. and inf., <i><span class="en">Od.
            8.516</span></i>.—II. intrans., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μάλ᾽
            ἀεῖσαι</span>, ‘merrily’, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λίγα,
            καλόν</span> (adv.); met. of the bow-string, <i><span class="en">Od. 21.411</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
